# C# mod conventions

- Target `netstandard2.1`; nullable reference types are enabled — honor nullability.
- Default to `internal` visibility; only expose what MelonLoader or other assemblies need.
- Namespace: `MimesisPlayerEnhancement.Features.{FeatureName}` for feature code.
- Use descriptive names (`approvedSaveSlotIds`, not `list` or `ids`) so intent is clear without reading surrounding code.
- Add brief comments for non-obvious business logic (host-only rules, game quirks, timing constraints).
- Do not create `.tmp-*` scratch projects — search `deps/decompiled/**/*` for game source; use MimesisReflectionTool for MelonLoader APIs.
- New features: register in `FeatureModules.All`, add config to `ModConfig.cs`, update [docs/CONFIG.md](../../docs/CONFIG.md).
- Run `make check` and `make debug` before considering changes complete.
- Match existing patterns: `_` prefix on private fields is used throughout this codebase — keep it consistent.
- Logging: default to `ModLog.Info/Debug/Warn/Error(Feature, message)` with a local `Feature` const; add `{Feature}Log.cs` only for shared formatting or repeated semantic events. See [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md#logging).
